abstract: A conservative watchdog group filed a complaint Wednesday with the Federal Election Commission alleging that Democratic Senate candidate John Hickenlooper improperly used footage from ads shot for his 2014 reelection campaign as Colorado governor in a video in August.
snippet: A conservative watchdog group filed a complaint Wednesday with the Federal Election Commission alleging that Democratic Senate candidate John Hickenlooper improperly used footage from ads shot for his 2014 reelection campaign as Colorado governor ...
lead_paragraph: DENVER — A conservative watchdog group filed a complaint Wednesday with the Federal Election Commission alleging that Democratic Senate candidate John Hickenlooper improperly used footage from ads shot for his 2014 reelection campaign as Colorado governor in a video in August.
headline_main: Conservatives Hit Colorado's Hickenlooper With FEC Complaint
headline_print_headline: Conservatives Hit Colorado's Hickenlooper With FEC Complaint

abstract: The Senate has confirmed two conservative, Justice Department lawyers to posts on a California-based appeals court that President Donald Trump has tagged as a liberal bastion.
snippet: The Senate has confirmed two conservative, Justice Department lawyers to posts on a California-based appeals court that President Donald Trump has tagged as a liberal bastion.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate has confirmed two conservative, Justice Department lawyers to posts on a California-based appeals court that President Donald Trump has tagged as a liberal bastion.
headline_main: Senate OKs Appeals Court Judges Over Home-State Opposition
headline_print_headline: Senate OKs Appeals Court Judges Over Home-State Opposition

abstract: Michael E. Horowitz, the Justice Department inspector general, told members of the Senate Judiciary Committee that his report was not a vindication of F.B.I. officials involved in the parts of the Russia investigation that he reviewed.

abstract: Andra Ursuta’s glass sculptures, Brice Marden’s latest paintings, portraits from Henry Taylor; Baseera Khan’s photo-collage constructions; and Jill Mulleady’s Neo-Surrealist works.
snippet: Andra Ursuta’s glass sculptures, Brice Marden’s latest paintings, portraits from Henry Taylor; Baseera Khan’s photo-collage constructions; and Jill Mulleady’s Neo-Surrealist works.
lead_paragraph: As a few giant galleries absorb ever more market share, thank the muses of art and commerce for Ramiken. The young dealer Mike Egan has piloted this enigmatic, protean gallery through a choppy decade for both art and real estate, and presented its ambitious exhibitions in a crumbling basement, an Upper East Side penthouse, a cave in Puerto Rico — and, now, a 17,000-square-foot warehouse floor in industrial Bushwick, Brooklyn, with a view of both refulgent skyscrapers and an infernal scrap-metal recycling plant.

abstract: Every purchase evokes his design of the rectangular Universal Product Code. But although it became ubiquitous, he received no royalties.
snippet: Every purchase evokes his design of the rectangular Universal Product Code. But although it became ubiquitous, he received no royalties.
lead_paragraph: George J. Laurer, whose design of the vertically striped bar code sped supermarket checkout lines, parcel deliveries and assembly lines and even transformed human beings, including airline passengers and hospital patients, into traceable inventory items, died on Dec. 5 at his home in Wendell, N.C., near Raleigh. He was 94.

abstract: An Arizona death row inmate was granted a new sentencing to consider evidence of childhood abuse. The justices examined whether that required a hearing in a trial court.
snippet: An Arizona death row inmate was granted a new sentencing to consider evidence of childhood abuse. The justices examined whether that required a hearing in a trial court.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Supreme Court on Wednesday struggled to decide what kind of new sentencing an Arizona death row inmate was entitled to after a federal appeals court ruled that the trial judge who had condemned him to death failed to take account of evidence of abuse the inmate had endured as a child.

abstract: Everywhere you look, there are cleaner, more private and more inclusive loos. Thank social justice warriors.
snippet: Everywhere you look, there are cleaner, more private and more inclusive loos. Thank social justice warriors.
lead_paragraph: In the past few years, something amazing has been quietly happening across the land. Public restrooms in America — long a flash point of exclusion by race, gender, class and ability — have gotten much, much better. Thanks to an increasingly effective campaign by a range of activists, America’s public bathrooms are now cleaner, more plentiful, more private, and more accessible and inclusive than ever. In many places, they’re even great.

abstract: U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement arrested fewer people during the 2019 budget year than last year, in part because resources were shifted to help handle the massive surge of migrants at the U.S.-Mexico border, the agency said Wednesday.
snippet: U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement arrested fewer people during the 2019 budget year than last year, in part because resources were shifted to help handle the massive surge of migrants at the U.S.-Mexico border, the agency said Wednesday.
lead_paragraph: DALLAS — U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement arrested fewer people during the 2019 budget year than last year, in part because resources were shifted to help handle the massive surge of migrants at the U.S.-Mexico border, the agency said Wednesday.
headline_main: ICE Arrested Fewer in 2019 as Resources Shifted to Border
headline_print_headline: ICE Arrested Fewer in 2019 as Resources Shifted to Border

abstract: With an executive order, he makes clear that anti-Semitism is not to be tolerated.
snippet: With an executive order, he makes clear that anti-Semitism is not to be tolerated.
lead_paragraph: As the poison of anti-Semitism spreads with dangerous violence throughout Europe, the Middle East, and even here at home — most recently in a horrific attack on Tuesday in Jersey City — President Trump is taking meaningful action to crush this evil.

abstract: Spain’s King Felipe VI on Wednesday asked caretaker Prime Minister Pedro Sánchez to try and form a government, even though the Socialist leader appeared short of political support.
snippet: Spain’s King Felipe VI on Wednesday asked caretaker Prime Minister Pedro Sánchez to try and form a government, even though the Socialist leader appeared short of political support.
lead_paragraph: MADRID — Spain’s King Felipe VI on Wednesday asked caretaker Prime Minister Pedro Sánchez to try and form a government, even though the Socialist leader appeared short of political support.
headline_main: Spanish King Invites Socialist Leader to Form a Government
